      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p>The papers of Samuel Wylie Crawford, physician and army officer, were
		  given to the Library of Congress by Eva Anderson Lawton, 1916-1918. An addition
		  was given by Luther M. Cornwall in 1939, and other material was purchased in
		  1915.</p>
      </acqinfo>
